description:
Like the mix? Click the [↻ Repost] button!

Hailing from Newcastle upon Tyne UK, Robert Patterson aka Syphon is a Drum & Bass DJ / Producer primarily focused on the deep and rolling sides of the genre. His mixes are characterised by a balance of creative harmonic blends giving each track room to breathe in the mix.
Syphon has performed live sets for Intrigue Music & Method Twenty Four, & his mixes have received support from the likes of Ben Soundscape, Tokyo Prose & GLXY.
Having recently released his debut track on Erculean Recordings with Russian producer AL_X, Syphon continues to hone his production skills whilst regularly serving up quality selections of deep liquid DnB on his Mixcloud page.

---

Originaire de Newcastle-upon-Tyne au Royaume-Uni, Robert Patterson alias Syphon est un DJ / Producteur Drum & Bass principalement axé sur les côtés deep et rolling du genre. Ses mixes sont caractérisés par un équilibre de mélanges harmoniques créatifs donnant à chaque track la possibilité de respirer dans le mix.
Syphon a joué des sets live pour Intrigue Music & Method Twenty Four, et ses mixes ont reçu le soutien de Ben Soundscape, Tokyo Prose & GLXY.
Ayant récemment sorti son premier morceau sur Erculean Recordings avec le producteur russe AL_X, Syphon continue de perfectionner ses compétences de production tout en offrant régulièrement des sélections DnB deep liquid de qualité sur sa page Mixcloud.

description:
Like the mix? Click the [↻ Repost] button!

Dava is a Dj and Producer from the southern German city of Freiburg. He started mixing around 2010 while playing in different clubs around Freiburg and soon became known for his diverse drum and bass and dubstep mixes. 

In 2012, Dava first started out producing dubstep. After a couple of  years, he developed an obsession with funky, soulful and deep drum and bass, which he’s been pursuing ever since. With releases on his hometown label Beatalistics Recordings, Celsius Recordings and Soul Deep Recordings under his belt, and many more to come in 2021, one can expect to keep encountering Dava’s name in the Drum and Bass scene in the future.

---

Dava est un DJ et producteur de la ville de Fribourg, dans le sud de l'Allemagne. Il a commencé à mixer vers 2010 tout en jouant dans différents clubs autour de Fribourg et s'est rapidement fait connaître au travers de ses divers mixs de drum & bass et de dubstep.

En 2012, Dava a commencé à produire du dubstep. Après quelques années, il a développé une obsession pour les côtés funky, soulful et deep de la drum & bass, qu'il poursuit depuis. Avec des sorties sur son label local Beatalistics Recordings, Celsius Recordings et Soul Deep Recordings à son actif, et bien d'autres à venir en 2021, on peut s'attendre à continuer à rencontrer le nom de Dava sur la scène Drum and Bass à l'avenir.

Big love to all locked in at the Show! Special shouts out to FX909, Dash Nick Tongue, Duoscience, Luciano - DnB, Wez dnb, QUMULUS and Kr33per and all the Labels supporting the MeditDnB imprint.

description:
GIRALDA is our newest release since last year’s single song KYRIE ELEISON. When I decided to spend my winter in the sleepy corner of Cadiz province in the south of Spain, I entered a harsh Corona winter. The entire town was often shrouded in freezing fog and there wasn't a soul to be seen on the streets. Inside the house, it was even more chilling. But I accommodated and fixed my place as a nice retreat after endless walks at the ocean, for work and to make music. Marking the beginning of my exile in Spain, these instrumental songs reflect the sound of the sea and the strong winds (Viento de Levante), my changes and the meditative state of the off-season village.
I listened to a lot of Dungeon Synth, Synthwave and soundtracks from John Carpenter movies during that time. Carpenter's music always had a huge impact on my musical style, since I grabbed a used copy of HALLOWEEN II in the Eighties. I can not get rid of the influence nor do I want to. The two songs on GIRALDA are also a love letter to Carpenter's work.
title: Giralda (Svantaal)

caption: Two Songs From The Edge Of The World

description:
AVAILABLE ON BEATPORT
https://www.beatport.com/release/imagination/3483444
———
UnBeat Records arrives, a digital record label, dedicated to Breakbeat and covers a wide range of aspects.
The first reference represents a double premiere since, it is also the first reference of Superbreaker

The first reference is by Superbreaker. A pseudonym in front of an artist with a long career in electronics, dedicated to other styles and who now lets out all the groove that he has accumulated since he was young and that he has rarely let out.

Imagination is a Breakbeat track in the purest 90s style, full of nuances and nods to top songs.
Energy and fun in equal parts where a super forceful rhythm sweeps, giving way to several sirens and alarms that catch our attention. A track in constant evolution that provides guaranteed fun time.

————————
SUPERBREAKER

A pseudonym at the head of an artist with a long career in electronics, dedicated to other styles and who now lets out all the groove that he has accumulated since he was young and that he has rarely let out.

It encompasses a multitude of styles within Breakbeat such as Hardcore, a variant of Happy Hardcore drawn towards House or Electro. Trip Hop and Hip Hop have been around a lot in the 90s with different formations.

A music collector from a very young age, he has gone through countless styles and musical stages, being Jazz and Funk constant throughout his career and, in turn, a source of inspiration and samples for his productions.

His work routine includes all kinds of technology that brings some sound and creativity. Akai's Mpcs are his favorite and that's where most of his rhythmic foundations come from. He tries to mix the feel of the Breakbeat songs of yesteryear with the modern sound provided by today's technology to remove that thorn nailed in his early production.

Despite the infinity of samples and phrases used in his productions, he always tries to emulate and include that sound from real instrument recordings. His musical knowledge allows him to play the piano, bass and guitar without becoming a master of any of them.

————————
UNBEAT RECORDS

UnBeat Records is a digital profile record label, dedicated to BreakBeat music in general and in turn is a sub-division of Guerrilla Records. Created to channel productions that do not fit in the line of the main label and thus make known productions that otherwise would not see the Light.

Based in Malaga, Andalusia, in the south of the peninsula, where in the 90s and part of the 2000s the BreakBeat sounded at full volume on every radio, car or rave, we could not avoid going through a stage of our youth in which the Broken rhythms will flood our lives We DJ, dance and produce thousands of hours and songs of this very energetic and special genre. We also enjoyed Drum & Bass and the evolution of Hip-Hop in the 90s.

All that remained in our musical DNA and today we need to air it and share it. That is the reason for being of UnBeat Records. Electro, hardcore, garage, drum & bass or jungle, among other genres, have a place in this new channel that follows the Guerrilla Records line. Underground essence where art and creativity are the epicenter. A channel where we can vent our primary artistic concerns such as drawing, photography, video art and, of course, music.

BEATPORT & SPOTIFY EXCLUSIVE

The Portals are the golden keys.
1. DANA, the key of charity and love immortal.
2. SHILA, the key of Harmony in word and act, the key that counterbalances the cause and the effect, and leaves no further room for Karmic action.
3. KSHANTI, patience sweet, that nought can ruffle.
4. VIRAGA, indifference to pleasure and to pain, illusion conquered, truth alone perceived.
5. VIRYA, the dauntless energy that fights its way to the supernal TRUTH, out of the mire of lies terrestrial.
6. DHYANA, whose golden gate once opened leads the Narjol toward the realm of Sat eternal and its ceaseless contemplation.
7. PRAJNA, the key to which makes of a man a God, creating him a Bodhisattva, son of the Dhyanis.

description:
https://youtu.be/mG-_Z-AxxxM for the visual EP journey of the tracks.

Hello hello hello hello

Human 2021 is the understanding that in order to come to a state of wholeness with one and other, we come from a state of being separated from one and other. This separation is hard, it’s divisive, it’s egoistic, it’s everything that makes you feel in isolation, quarantined. It’s designed this way. This is the purpose of duality.

“I also get lost in this chaos of transitioning and my ego loves a good narrative that makes me feel righteous about what I think is wrong or right in this world. I want to sincerely respect that my vessel was chosen for this work to come through and also respect the other vessels that were inspired to journey along. Please assist me as you already have in carving this new path inside even deeper. Help me develop a sense for connection with others, above our differences. We are one.”  Seun

There is no reality in the world besides Godliness and all the concealment is only in ones sensations.

There is no time in spirituality.
We experience time as a real thing in our current frequency, the frequency of this world. With this said, if a peaceful, unified and corrected state is in our future, wether you believe it to be in this world or the next. Then we are already in that state, we just have to see it, shift our frequency . For example, see it this way. Imagine you were born in a world that has only ever played Highveld stereo 94.7fm. The world is the radio, the device, it has other frequencies to tune into but you have only ever been told about 94.7fm. Does that mean Jacaranda fm or 5fm doesn’t exist?

In other words, the end is already in the preliminary thought. It’s all one and happens at the same time.

Do we become human once we start seeing through the illusion of being separate? Do we lift ourselves from this animalistic, physical, fragile state of existence once we wake up and start making actions towards overriding this egoistic software and install the qualities of the Creator force between us? Change the station?

Overriding our current nature or software or frequency is by no means an easy task. But we have come to such states in the world where we can’t help but to ask the question..... why are we here? Did we come here to suffer, hate each other because of our differences, catch vir#@!es and watch what we care about most in our lives crumble and die away? Highlighting not only our fragile physical states but especially our dangerous mental states.

It has become very clear that individually we can not control what happens outside of us. The mind control wether you stand on the left or the right is as clear as daylight. Maybe that’s exactly what we need, light. Light shines on the dark, it exposes it. We are living through very special times, light is beaming through to this planet, shifting our collective frequency. 
Whatever you see when the lights come on, if you see division, hate, poverty, manipulation and so on, in any layer of your life. Then you are being shown what we as a collective humanity need to face.
But first face these things inside of us before we demand and protest for the outside to change.

The power lies within and between us.
If we discover love in the “Social distance” between us, nothing bad can exist.
No matter what narrative you are manipulated into believing, once we start creating love between us, only truth can exist. The current system or frequency is a teacher, showing us the consequences if we don’t unite. Like a parent who sometimes lets the child fall so they can learn through the experience of consequences. How many times do we still need to fall?

This is Human 2021

Let’s continue to  create narratives of unity and connection.

We are all on this journey to be whole.

theartofconnection.co
title: Becoming Human - Seun

description:
Welcome to May's selection of melodic Progressive and uplifting house with present through to past sounds..
New music from Nora En Pure, Lane 8, Maur, Sian Evans, Audio-jack and more..  Then we dip into the past with our feature mix devoted to the uplifting sound of the Piano with big riffs and a nod to the old skool :-) 120 mins non stop for the car, the gym, a walk a run, or feet up and immerse in the magical world of dance music. Thanks for checking in.
title: The Mix Sessions May 21 - Beat 106 Scotland

caption: New Sounds woven around some classic remixes and reworks,. and we spotlight perfect productions.
description: 120 Minutes, House & Electronica with a few exclusive reworks for this show only! Tracks from Andrew Bayer, DJ Dan, The Groove Technicians, Ben Bohmer, Bronson, The Deepshakerz, PLUS a feature mix on Perfecto productions as I share some encounters with Paul Oakenfold over the years and cover my top 5 from Oakey & Osbourne. As always appreciate you stopping by and please share and spread the word. Thanks, Colin.
title: The Mix Sessions March 21 - Beat 106 - Listen again

caption: Electronica and piano grooves back to back,. its the Mix Sessions for 21 HNY!
description:
New Year - new Mix show,.. as we ease into 21 with a blend of Progressive beats, the best Electronica and driving Piano Grooves. Music from York, David Jackson, Nora En Pure, Christoph, Roland Clark and many more..
Thanks for stopping by - 2 hours take with you on the move or plug in and sit back ;-)
tag_list: "Progressive House" "piano house" classics Remixes "mash ups" electronica
title: The Mix Sessions Jan 21 - Beat 106 Listen again!

description: Dec Instalment of House & Electronica - The MIX Sessions featuring music from Sam Holland, Tinlicker, Camelphat, Nora En Pure and reworked classics from Offshore and Frankie Knuckles,.. BIG Guest mix from House legend Kris Keegan with a bunch of upfront jackin house grooves and catchy vocals.. Thanks as always for all the playbacks and the support, have great festive period. Colin.
title: The Mix Sessions Dec 20 - Beat 106 Scotland

caption: The old & the new - 2 hours on demand in the car, the gym, the Kitchen.. enjoy.
description:
A Blended Mix this as always, the old and the new with some edits and spur of the moment mash ups! 
We delve into the vault for a classic Feature Mix from the Space Brothers from 2000 - Worthy of a replay from this legendary duo still sounding great. 
Music from Christoph, Tinlicker, JJ Mula, Alan Dixon, Solarstone, TestPress, Mrs & Mrs smith, Orson Welsh and more. 
Thanks to everyone for taking time to check out.

description:
Ooi meus queridos e Feliz Aniversario para mim!

Vocês não imaginam o prazer que é estar de volta, e voltei com tudo com esse meu set mix feito especialmente para o meu aniversario de 3.0! Sim hoje é meu aniversario mas o presente é pra vocês!

Quero agradecer a todos envolvidos, desde a minha nova logo a Josy Hope, a capa do set mix Carlos Alberto... Aos Djs Anndhy Backer, Márcio Peron, Apolo Oliver, Celso Duarte, Kaleb Sampaio, Lucas Monteiro, Diogo Ferrer, Erick Galdino entre outros outros que produziram tracks INCRIVEIS. E aos pouquíssimos amigos que me deram apoio de alguma forma e em especial ao meu Amigo e DJ, Wendell Ribeiro incentivou para esse meu retorno.

Espero que curtam e muito e uma boa vibe para todos!

Lockdown got me missing downtown 
What kind of town is a ghost town 
Die now

Outro

Hey look mother, i found the last vaccine in the world,
now you are safe, forever... Wait...

Written by Saulo Ol. S.
title: Lockdown

description:
Memory Lane 
 
Janet wife of Johnson James 
Just came ‘jingling’ his name 
Darling though it isn't more than just another day 
We are already all ready there 
 
The little daughter droped the water  
The bees on flowers powdering nectar While the guitar of father Hector was weeping  
To the despair of grandpa who couldn't smoke because his hands were shaking  
 
One of the kids finally fishes a fish And the fish's speech is that he can grant a wish  
To the kid who, then, put him free  And now the fish will wash the dishes since kid wished 
 
And all the joy ending with some comic disaster Like the dog robing food or someone twisting the earring into aunt Loiu's braids 
"We will be together", so they swear  
But they ignored that time is always there replacing share, replacing care  
For disregard to that country fair... Of sweet despair 
 
And as the time is passing by just like a cloud on cloudy sky When you realise will be too late to wonder why 
 
And the polaroid pictures that you own 
Of passed nights in campfire songs 
All the memories about the streets where you grew up remains the same 
You now call affecnionately memory lane 

 
Written by Saulo Oliveira S.
title: Memory Lane

description:
Cosmic Jive 
 
A girl lies peacefully in the morning 
There’s a hell of rain outside  
She barely heard the cold wind calling 
It’s all out of her sight 
 
A boy is lost and without any map 
He desperately needs a wrench  
His car is broken and totally flat 
There’s a screw he needs to clench 
 
He quickly knocks at the girl's door 
She thought he was one of a kind 
“Is he that someone that I’ve been looking for? 
I think I will have to find” 
 
She puts the kettle on to Earl Grey 
He think she is divine 
The night is young and he could stay 
'Cause now she is singing Cymbaline 
 
The street lamp goes out making 
Her light up a candle in time 
He can't stay cause his mom is waiting 
“I’ll have to decline” 
 
She says have a safe trip back  
To your distant hometown  
But what she says inside in fact 
Is “don’t leave me now” 

 
 
She is holding an empty heart and soul 
As he waves going down  
The loneliness like a cancer grows 
As the wind begins to howl 
 
 
A girl lies depressively in the night 
She wonder “will he and his mom be fine?” 
A motherless boy tricked by a cosmic jive 
Is wondering “Why did I declined?” 
 
Cosmic jive 
All the time 
A cosmic jive 
 
It was that what 
Caught us  
In that time 
 
In that time 
In that time 
In that time 
In that time 
In that time 
In that time 
Cosmic jive 
 
Written by Saulo Oliveira S.
title: Cosmic Jive

description:
Lyrics

I still can hear you calling me to go outside to see the stars
I still can hear you telling me to put the catle on for Earl Grey
But what I'm hearing is not true if you're not really here
And I'll keep wishing that you where here

In my mind you are here and we are all together
Hearing songs, singing the blues
Complaining of this (London's) weather

In my mind you never left
In my books, you're always there
When I walk to television I can see your face
'Cause that actress has exactly the same ways that you used to do

When I'm alone, you're there too
'Cause your perfume in all the room
No one really stands alone...

Come back home and lets sing the blues again
Come back home and just lets sing the blues again 
Come back home and just lets spend the days in rain again
Like we used to do... Like we used to do

Written by Saulö Oliveira S.
title: Like We Used To Do

description:
You shoudn't blame me for this war
Cause I voted on Al Gore
At least that year I can say I tried
And then the court was the one who decided

There's no democracy
Left or Right, you say the anarchy
Could turn it bright

I dreamed a dream
Where we lived in a red world with equality
All in common, red brick houses, in our perfect synchrony

Free the working class hero man, give him the Nobel
Power to the people, here and there
I got some red ideas to share

Thunderbirds...

Thunderbirds are far to fly...

You came to tell me that life is awful
Too much intolerance, war and blood
But you're the one who chose the fascists
And you're the one who governs behind them

And your thirst for blood governs behind them
And your greed for greener grass, governs behind them

Behind them...
Behind them...

Written and composed by Saulo Oliveira S.

This is the first part of a political opera rock. Here the communism is praised and the fascism is rejected, a particular vision of the writer. In the second part, KKK, the upcoming track, adults are no longer available to govern on the Earth and, then, the kids are setting the rules, torturing and killing adults, a kind of distopia, based on classic literature such as "Lord of The Flies", "Animal Farm" and  "Children of Corn'.
title: What Governs Behind Them?

description:
Lyrics

LD MTV

Back at the childhood 
I used to draw and read “The Mocker”
But how to be nostalgic
If can no more see Mark Knopfler

Used to jump out of the school 
Just to watch MTV
Used to curse and break the rules
Bullying that nerd Stevie

There we were wasting time
All days long on dungeons and dragons
Playing some stupid scenes 
Jerking off over playboy magazines 

But how to not be nostalgic if some good stuff has changed 
The videos on television 
They should had stayed the same
So the only thing I’m asking is to put it there again
The mainstream should break free
Cindy Lauper or The Police 
Playing on MTV

Then my wife came and said 
Stop complaining, you sound so rude
And I yelled echoing
“I don’t want to get it on YouTube”

 Back there grandpa mocked
“Isn’t he young to be singing the blues”?
“This boy has been brainwashed”
Grandpa, you don’t even have a clue!

We could have a time machine 
For a moments just like that 
What’s the matter to play on the radio
“Out of the blue and into the black”?

Back at the childhood
I understand this a changing world 
Rolling stone gathers no moss
There’s more than the eye can see
But all I’m begging here
Is bring back my old MTV

Written and composed by Saulo Oliveira S.
title: Old MTV

description:
"City Drums Radio show" is a podcast hosted by Uri Mood and focused on electronic music, specifically House, Afro house and Tech-house.

Uri Mood has been playing in the best clubs of Barcelona and Spain since the late 90s, and through house and tech music, making people dance has been a passion.

The philosophy of his music can be defined with one phrase:

“I´d like to go back to the roots of House music, electronic music is not only about dancing, it is feeling and understanding that music can contain a message beyond the rhythm.

Welcome to the City Drums.

El programa de radio "City Drums Radio Show" es un podcast presentado por Uri Mood y enfocado en la música electrónica, específicamente House, Afro house y Tech-house.

Uri Mood ha tocado en los mejores clubes de Barcelona y España desde finales de los 90, y a través de la música house y tech, hacer bailar a la gente ha sido una pasión.

La filosofía de su música se puede definir con una frase:

“Me gustaría volver a las raíces del House, la música electrónica no es solo bailar, es sentir y entender que la también puede contener un mensaje más allá del ritmo"

Bienvenidos a City Drums.
title: City Drums Radio Show (#EP09) - Hosted and Mixed by Uri Mood

I know you think that the world is over their heads, you're always thinking you're so right.
You justify the hate you're spouting,
but I refuse to just walk on by tonight.
I cannot let this go any longer.
People like you put this chip on my shoulder.
I gotta stand up for the rights of everyone around me, hate mongerer.
Hate mongerer.

[Refrain]
I refuse to let you stand there!
Claim to be Godly, how is unequal treatment fair?
You don't care about the lives of others,
you just want a front row chair!

You spout the scripture like it's a bullet.
Maybe you need to take to heart what you say!
The book you read from, you've skewed its meaning.
All of the hatred and violence, throw it away!
Your interpretation, it leaves me invalid.
Because the love of God doesn't stop at a demographic.
You need to check your balance between love and wrath.
Hate mongerer, hate mongerer.

[Refrain]

If Jesus Christ stood before you, showing you his loving ways,
I bet you would spit in his face and say he'll burn in hell!

You wouldn't know God if he slapped you in the face.
How did I ever walk by in the first place?
I cannot keep my head down any longer.
You've helped me find my purpose, hate mongerer.
My purpose here is not to live in a lie.
My purpose here is not to just walk on by.
My purpose here is to make the wrong right.
Spread love and kindness, but also to fight against people like you
that do what you do,
shaming everyone when you need to focus on you.

description: as the vengeful spirit of a deformed man who was tragically killed by his father on Halloween night. Victor Crowley was conceived through an affair involving his father, Thomas, and Lena, the nurse of his terminally ill wife, Shyann. When Shyann Crowley learned of her husband's infidelity, she placed a curse on the unborn Victor just before she died. As a result of the curse, Victor was born horribly disfigured, and Lena died the moment she laid eyes on him. Thomas raised Victor lovingly despite his deformity, and kept him hidden from the outside world to keep other children from tormenting him. Years later, Sampson Dunston, his brother, and his friend Trent Graves threw firecrackers at the Crowley house to scare Victor out, causing the house to catch fire. Thomas tried to save Victor, but accidentally struck him in the face with a hatchet. Due to the violent nature of his death, Victor became a ghost eternally reliving the night, searching for his father and killing anyone he sees, becoming a local legend, and only able to die when part of the family of those that killed him gave him his father.

description:
Tyler Jack is a breath of fresh air on the UK electronic music scene, having already stormed his native Ireland with a series of energetic shows coupled with a musical knowledge beyond his years and an enthusiastic approach that's all too rare in clubs in 2021.

Having first raised the attention of promoters in Belfast, Northern Ireland with his weekly streams on Facebook, his grasp of social media has enabled the young upstart to cultivate an organic fanbase of thousands from the comfort of his own studio. Joining the dots between techno, trance and hardstyle whilst still having a respect and understanding of the classics, you can almost forget you are listening to an artist barely in his teenage years.

Follow me on Social Media
Facebook - www.facebook.com/djtylerjack
Instagram - www.instagram.com/tylerjackmusic
Soundcloud - www.soundcloud.com/tylerjackmusic

description:
The trance version of the track called Roller Coaster, of which there is also a bounce version, both of them sharing common elements but going in different directions.

Common elements include the rhythmic base (inspired, in part, by the Speed Garage), bass and drop. But above all what they share is that the some main sounds go up and down constantly, giving the feeling of being in an amusement park, hence its name.

Instead, the versions convey different sensations. While the bounce is more upbeat, playful and bouncy this version is a bit more serious and includes a melody.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
La versión trance del tema llamado Roller Coaster, del que también existe una versión bounce. Cada uno de ellos comparte elementos comunes pero se dirigen en direcciones diferentes.

Los elementos comunes incluyen la base rítmica (inspirada, en parte, en el Speed Garage), el bajo y el drop. Pero sobre todo lo que comparten es que algunos sonidos principales suben y bajan constantemente, dando la sensación de estar en un parque de atracciones, de ahí su nombre.

En cambio, las versiones transmiten sensaciones diferentes. Mientras que la bounce es más alegre, jugetón y saltarín esta versión es algo más seria e incluye una melodía.

[lyrics]
that's mr. what's-it-to-ya, and he knows everything
he'll ask you where you're going, he won't ask where you've been
well, i've been in the forest
i'm not sure where to go
been thinking about taking a walk and lying in the snow

take your eyes off the wheel
look at me time and time again, didn't you know that?
i was never one of your friends
it's upsetting so quickly, dialing numbers on my phone (you)
might die while in the moment, but nobody really lost you

that's mr. what's-it-to-ya, and he knows everything
he'll ask you where you're going, he won't ask where you've been
so when your wallet's empty, he might lend you a hand
so when you get lost, regret the time you spent

that's not the plan, i'm just praying i don't lose my head
i'll end up dead and i'll promise i'll be back by ten
my face turns red
get out the car with something that i kept, but you know

it's almost a story, i ripped out the pages (i ripped out some pages)
their life was so boring, they moved somewhere vacant (they moved somewhere, fake it)
they must be so worried, all about their baby
i'm your little baby (that's what you said to me)

what's it gonna take to get away?
you feel this way, don't even care how late it is
what entered your head to make you this way?
you feel this way, do you even care for your safety?

just keep walking down the road, nobody's gonna call you
the truck nearly hit me, but it wasn't out of luck: "you..."
the sun's setting so quickly, dialing numbers on my phone (you)
might die while in the moment, but nobody really lost you

caption: New release with the wonderful Shauni 🤟
description:
Release Date: 12/05/2021

Pre-Save/Streaming Link: https://ffm.to/bon-psy-shauni-blum

Born out of reflection and a keen observation of life, Blüm is the latest collaboration between artist/producer, Bon-Psy & Singer/Songwriter, Shauni.

Having already released a series of introspective and thought-provoking tracks, Bon-Psy continues chipping away at his unique style to unearth new ways of presenting his sources of inspiration. Shauni returns here fresh off the back of 'Disappear', once again embellishing her R&B infused vocals in a stand out performance. 

Inspired by the life of a flower, Bon-Psy navigates varying emotional states that capture the essence of the journey through existence. Joy, grief, despair, love & hope. Blüm depicts what it is to be alive in movie esque fashion, with singer Shauni providing a poignant narrative that unifies the lifecycle of a flower with our own lives as human beings. 

Blüm is once again a stellar release for these two artists who work in synergy to translate the journey of life into music.

'Despite the garden you've been dealt, it's still a garden. Your garden. When it feels you have nothing left to give, water it with a new perspective and watch what blooms there. Here you can allow your flowers to grow toward the sun into brighter days.'
tag_list: electronica electronic "experimental electronic" "experimental electronica" Bon-Psy Shauni Blüm IDM "Future Beats" Experimental
title: Bon-Psy & Shauni - Blüm

description:
Release Date: 19/02/2021

Pre-Save/Streaming Link: https://ffm.to/serene

Bon-Psy & Visco City, two of the most exciting new artists within the Experimental Electronica scene, work together in harmonious fashion on their latest release ‘Serene’. 

Both artists, having seen great success in 2020, effortlessly blend their two unique styles together to create something magical. ‘Serene’ is a rollercoaster, an amalgamation of different styles that they are able to effortlessly weave in and out of. Here they find balance between their approaches, and the result is five minutes of Electronic bliss.

Whilst ‘Serene’ is a standout release on its own, the accompanying Music Video presents further material to be dissected. Each section of the video corresponds to the four total lunar eclipses preceding the extremely rare “Blood Moon”. The alignment of the moon with the sun is a rare occurrence, and much like ‘Serene’ is an experience to be in awe of. Fleeting doves in each section suggest harmony, the rarity of a “Blood Moon” personifies the unlikeliness of two producers flourishing together so well.

Bon-Psy & Visco City kick off 2021 with grace and style, ‘Serene’ is an exciting proposal of what is yet to come.
tag_list: Electronic Electronica Experimental "Experimental Electronic" Serene Bon-Psy "Visco City" "Future Beats" Idm "Experimental Electronica"
title: Bon-Psy & Visco City - Serene

caption: My latest single 'Ikigai' is out now, enjoy everyone! 🤟😁
description:
Release Date: 13/11/2020

Streaming Link: https://ffm.to/bon-psy-ikigai

British producer Bon-Psy is back again with another grandiose production off the back of ‘Onyx’.

‘Ikigai’ (the Japanese concept related to finding one’s purpose), is a leap into uncharted territory in the Experimental Electronic scene, and once again an artist defining piece nailing down the staples of the Bon-Psy sound.

A sprawling exploration of the depths of Electronica, ‘Ikigai’ is mosaic in nature, presenting a driving groove, majestic vocal lines and goose bump inducing progressions that are nothing short of a spectacle.

With this new single, the young artist takes strides into discovering his capabilities as a musician, but also, identifying his purpose as a human being.
tag_list: Electronic Electronica Experimental Euphoric Japan Bon-Psy Ikigai "Experimental Electronic" Piano Chills "Future Beats" Idm Melodic Beats
title: Bon-Psy - Ikigai

Alek Sandar and Andrea team up with producer, Bon-Psy, to return with 'Never Be The Same Again - Bon-Psy Remix'. 

Alek seeing previous success with tracks ‘Yerba', ‘Hey Mami’, and ‘Ti Si Nai’ collaborates with Andrea who is known for her hits, 'Haide Hopa", "Upotrobena", "Heart Beating Hard". 

‘Never Be The Same Again - Bon-Psy Remix’ is a spin on the 2000 hit by Spice Girl, Melanie C. and the late, TLC group member, Lisa 'Left Eye' Lopes. 

The captivating electronica sound showcases the beginning of a new path less traveled for two people and entices new discoveries and memories together.

description:
This is me, again, with a new release on Happy Hardcore Underground Volume 2! This time, I went with a nod to the 90s Happy Hardcore sound - with uplifting synths, piano riffs and bright vocals!

Get this track in the extended mix, alongside this bundle with other 19 amazing tracks, on this link:

https://hardcoreunderground.co.uk/store/view/HUDIGI058

About Happy Hardcore Underground Volume 2:

We think you'll agree that this collection of tracks, a big chunk of which are totally exclusive to this project, have been well worth the wait. Pianos, breakbeats, stabs, rap samples, hands in the air moments and plenty of that original Happy Hardcore vibe is what we've tried to make sure is present in every track. Whatever twists and turns Hardcore takes, so much of which we love, there'll always be a place for this sound.

description:
Artist: Gade System
Release Title: C-SEC
Tracks: 3
Label: EXE Project
Cat Number: EXE-D006

Release Date: October 29th 2021
Format: Digital (WAV)

Production: Gade System
Mastering: Aaron Spectre

Graphic Design: Machine™

EXE Project proudly welcomes the debut release from Stuttgart based electronic music producer: Gade System. Known previously to many as ‘Breakforce One’ Gade System’s inception was born from the producer's desire to push his sound design skills to create a cleaner, more dynamic output into drum & bass and beyond.

C-SEC presents 3 slabs of rich sonic energy, with the single ‘Fireback’ being presented as a long-form cinematic experience at the same time as remaining totally impactful as a high-energy drum and bass piece. 

Following this ‘The Raid’ evolves perfectly from the previous track delivering a well-executed example of ‘tension and release’ with superb sound design and incredible attention to detail. 

The final track ‘Social Hour’ - offers a hammer-blow of half-time rhythms and bass. The saturated Reece wraps around the cumbersome pacing of the drums, creating an over-driven, slow-moving monolith of a track.

EXE-D006 represents another leap forward for EXE Project and their unique high-concept, high-energy output. Pushing both science fiction themes and the boundaries of cinematic sound design into the nightclubs and dance floors.

Available via Bandcamp from the 29th of October and all other digital stores from the 8th of November.

www.exe-project.com
tag_list: Neurofunk halftime gade system exe Project
title: EXE-D006 - Gade System - Fireback

Take me back to when we wished
On shooting stars, on shooting stars
Chasing dreams that were
Never too far, never too far

I won’t let you down, I won't let you down again
So just take my hand and follow me back in
I don't wanna lose, I don't wanna lose this chance

It could be wonderful and so lovely
Just don’t give up on me

I still miss that time
Feeling the touch of your skin
Your fingers entwined with mine
Vivid memories that keep me alive
Just like a fairytale

No matter how my heart aches
And all that may come between;
These pages were written for you and me
I gaze out to the skies and see
The pages flipping through our happy ending

description:
To you the ROAR Crew,

We are proud and humbled to today celebrate ROAR's first birthday - by bidding you farewell, and sending out a MASSIVE thank you for all of your support, in whatever shape that took, since our launch this time last year.

ROAR was always meant to be a lockdown project to bring a smile to the faces of ravers while journalistically chronicling the rave scene - and with raves on their way back, lockdown (sort of) lifting, and Latch expecting his second kid in September and having to do some paid work, our first birthday this week seemed a good time to wind it up...for now at least.

Proudly, we bow out having achieved a huge amount. That includes chronicling the '90s rave scene by interviewing in great depth - often for the first time - many of the legends who created the Decade of Rave; all our episodes being curated into the BRITISH LIBRARY SOUND ARCHIVE for future historians or rave obsessives; having our content viewed or listened to HALF A MILLION TIMES in a year, with some interviews being viewed or heard more than 20,000 times; bringing together a community of 5,000 subscribers on YouTube and similar again on social media; giving new talent a chance to shine and supporting the scene's recent resurgence; and, most importantly, bringing joy and entertainment to the rave scene at a bleak time for us all where we couldn't go out raving.

As you'll hear in this farewell episode, while we are halting the crowdfund for obvious reasons, Latch will be keeping the ROAR website and channel open for as long as he can afford to do so, and we are not against creating future content, should the right opportunities arise...in fact, we may drop some stuff from time to time so do keep your eyes peeled!

We will happily continue to put out more ROAR TRACK ATTACKS as long as producers keep sending them - send them to hello [at] roaruk [dot] com.

And if you know any businesspeople or wealthy philanthropists who'd like to help keep the project alive, even by allowing us to take on a young trainee, then we are all ears - again, it's hello [at] roaruk [dot] com.

[Also, if you'd like to donate even a few quid from time to time to help Latch keep the website live - as it costs a few hundred quid a year to merely exist - you can do so at https://www.paypal.com/roaruk.]

We had hoped to depart by interviewing CARL COX and SHARKEY, but unfortunately events and timings conspired against us - so apologies for that. Happily, though, Sharkey is well and back where he belongs at the heart of the hardcore scene, and that's the most important thing.

However, our most recent interview, where DnB impresario LONDON ELEKTRICITY talks for the first time about last summer's racism storm which engulfed his label, HOSPITAL RECORDS, is one of our best so far so check it out if you've not already - https://soundcloud.com/roarukpods/episode-54-hospital-records-ceo-london-elektricity-33-weathering-a-potentially-fatal-storm

There are loads of people to thank for their help bringing this project to fruition and keeping it going over the past 18 months - as we do in this episode, and apologies if anyone was missed out - but without you guys at home watching, commenting, subscribing and also donating your money during a tough time financially, none of this would have happened. 

So thanks a million yet again, and if we don't see you on here, we will hopefully see you on a dancefloor! 

Loads of love,

ROAR HQ x
title: Happy Birthday, Thank You & Goodbye from ROAR x

description:
HOSPITAL RECORDS co-founder & CEO, LONDON ELEKTRICITY, speaks publicly in an interview for the very first time about allegations of racism that consumed the label in the wake of George Floyd’s murder and the Black Lives Matter movement, in this the final part of ROAR’s engrossing marathon three-parter with one of the most influential figures in rave music.

The DJ & producer - AKA TONY COLMAN - admits he was initially “furious” Hospital had been accused of being a racist organisation by Black former employee CHRIS INPERSPECTIVE, which went viral online causing a huge storm in the jungle drum and bass scene.

Although admitting Hospital did not at that time employ any BAME staff, Tony rejects the notion he or anyone at the label is racist and felt they unfairly become the focus of a wider societal backlash despite other big DnB labels having less diverse artist rosters than them. Coming though at a sensitive moment for global racial equality, Tony feared Hospital might not survive at all.

Yet more than a year on, with the label still going strong even amid a pandemic that has stopped most live music events, Tony concedes Hospital could and should have done better, and even says he’s “glad” to have gone through it because he’s spent the past year educating himself, and putting in place policies to improve the situation, including plans to create a more diverse board of directors at Hospital.

Unveiling some of his musical plans for the future and discussing what the scene might look like post-pandemic, Tony - who is stepping back from running he label to focus on DJing and production - swore Hospital will never be sold to a major label and will always remain independent.

Hospital, he says, is always on the look for diverse new talent and he told young jungle DnB artists to get in touch if they want their tunes released on the label. Producers, you know what to do….

description:
HOSPITAL RECORDS co-founder and CEO TONY COLMAN reveals exclusively to ROAR about his decision to step down after a difficult last year, in part 2 of our exclusive mega-interview.

Some 12 months after the label was caught in a storm of allegations of racism, Tony - AKA DJ and producer LONDON ELEKTRICITY explains he wants to focus on performing and producing as he moves into his sixties.

Beginning with a discussion about how his label’s rise coincided with New Labour’s landslide 1997 General Election win - which was set to the sound-track of D:Ream’s Things Can Only Get Better - and ‘Cool Britannia’, he admits the sometimes moody jungle scene came close to being toppled by garage.

But instead of that happening, Tony states his belief that garage actually saved drum and bass by removing some of what he saw as the troublesome and violent elements.

He also recalls his highs and lows of his DJing career - including one set where he was too drunk to play, which saw him stop drinking before performing - and talks about the thrill he gets from giving opportunities to new acts.

In the final part, coming FRIDAY, Tony will exclusively address for the first time in an interview those allegations of racism from last Summer. So please stay right to the end of the interview, because it's not one to miss!

description:
ROAR gets typically deep with LONDON ELEKTRICITY, one of the most influential names in the current drum and bass jungle scene, and co-founder of arguably its biggest label HOSPITAL RECORDS.

Through his work Hospital, the DJ, producer and event promoter - AKA TONY COLMAN - has been hailed by some for changing the face of drum and bass and jungle by helping push it to a more mainstream audience. But last year Tony and the label faced allegations of racism by a Black former staff member and the wider public.

In this mega three-part interview no stone will be left unturned and no issue left unaddressed as he speaks for the first time about his “difficult” year, and reveals it has led him to step back from running the business.

In this episode, Tony will talk about how as a “born rebel” he defied the wishes of his “buttoned up” parents to forge a career in the underground music scene, and was inspired by GOLDIE’s TIMELESS album to bring his love of avant-garde acid jazz to the tough and sometimes unwelcoming jungle scene where he initially felt like an outsider desperate to be accepted...but first had to teach himself how to produce the stuff!

Explaining how Hospital came to pass, and its “accidental” success, Tony will tell how the label came up with its iconic name and stood out from the crowd with its famous bright and bold artwork and designs. 

In part 2 Tony will talk of how, along with Goldie, RONI SIZE, and a few notable others, Hospital helped change the image of jungle drum and bass from a scene with a reputation for violence in the late ‘90s, by forging its own path, reveal some of his highs and lows as a DJ and producer, and discuss his decision to step back from running the label.
 
And in the third and final part Tony will exclusively address for the first time in an interview those allegations of racism from last Summer. So do stay with us right to the end of the interview, because you will not want to miss it!

description:
Rave originator JUMPING JACK FROST rounds up his three-part interview with ROAR by moving into the modern day and assessing the many positives, and some negatives, of the current drum and bass scene, while comparing the then and now.

Praising ANDY C for his huge success which continues to push the music into the mainstream, Frost - AKA NIGEL THOMPSON - also addresses recent claims of racism and ‘whitewashing’ which came to the fore when his label V RECORDINGS was not featured in last year’s Drum and Bass Arena documentary about the history of the scene, and why  until recently there have historically been so few female rave artists.

Nigel also chats about what a tough year it’s been for DJs - although it’s been pretty good for V, he says - and how he’s managed lockdown despite losing several people close to him to Covid-19.

And he talks about his latest project, the excellent FROST REPORT, which sees him and other notable public figures discuss a range of issues including racism, women’s rights, and mental health - while also giving advice to aspiring producers.

Next Friday we bring you the first of a three-part interview with HOSPITAL RECORDS founder, DJ and producer, LONDON ELEKTRICITY (AKA TONY COLMAN), who will address publicly for the first time the wave of allegations of racism which the label went through last summer, as well as how - like Frost - he helped change jungle and drum and bass.

Frost’s artwork today was drawn by DnB Illustrated. Check her out at https://www.instagram.com/dnbillustra...

ENJOY ALL THIS GREAT RAVE CONTENT? You can support us and get perks in return via https://www.patreon.com/ROARUKPods,, or donate anything you can on a monthly or one-off basis via PayPal - https://www.paypal.com/roaruk

TRANCESPIRED DARK - 
Malaysian producer, Syafiq Hakim is a name which many in the harder, tech-trance scene will recognise and we are delighted to have him on-board at Trancespired Dark.

"Dark Raven" is a manic tech banger with thumping kicks, perfect rolling bass and a plethora of fx and samples which maintains your interest throughout the whole crazy 6 and a half minutes. Even manages to add a contrasting uplifting-style break before launching back into the madness!

A perfect addition to any tech-trance dj's arsenal.

Supported by: Suzy Solar, Mickey Marr, DJ Laura May, David McQuiston, Carlos Martz, Mike Crawley Music, DJ Brisk and more.

caption: When you get invited to a Halloween house party, you know you can go hard af! Shuffling, headbanging, and having an amazing night.
description:
TRACKLIST: https://go.plurth.com/mahalloween2021 (for some reason soundcloud URL links aren't working, copy this link and paste in browser)
Finally, Halloween is back in full force! This means that our annual Mahalloween DJ mix series that spans 8 years now is back too! We are very appreciative and grateful to our friend cogirlaspen ( https://www.instagram.com/cogirlaspen/ ) and her rave fam who invited us to play a private costume contest house party. All we can say is that it went OFF! One of the best parties we've ever played because the crowd was feeling the vibes and dancing hard on the rooftop looking over Downtown Denver. Revelers were shuffling, headbanging, and having an amazing night while we played a selection of originals, remixes, and some of our favorite Halloween bangers. Props to @on11music for throwing down a dirty bass set to keep the party going!

description:
Beatport Pre-Order: https://www.beatport.com/release/wtf/3549378
Beatport Exclusive: Friday 12th November 2021
Global Release: Friday 26th November 2021

Mexican trance supremo, Allan McLuhan, kicked off the Trancespired Dark label last year so it was high time we had him back to assault your senses.

"WTF?" certainly lives up to the title as it launches it's no-holds-barred approach straight for the jugular. A plethora of fx, tech elements, vocal samples and acid bombard you and that's just the beginning. For us, the standout section in the track is found in the break with that wickedly haunting riff - serious oooft!

If you like it hard and manic, then Allan has delivered to you in spades.

description:
Buy or Stream: https://smarturl.it/TD010
Beatport direct: https://www.beatport.com/release/interstellar/3501463

Well, after a long lay-off we are back, and we are back with a bang as we welcome manic Mexican producer, Impulse Wave to the stable.

Those who are well aware of this fantastic producer will know what to expect in "Interstellar". Awesomely hard kick and bass, accompanied by sfx and oodles of atmosphere are the order of the day here as Impulse Wave takes you on a galactic journey. There are sections of lightened relief in the beautiful break where the main melody is introduced which then continues in the floor-filling drop!

Absolute peach of a release which will certainly appeal to those of a hard trance persuasion.

description:
Beatport Exclusive: https://www.beatport.com/release/2-th3-proteus/3252577
Global Release: Tuesday 26th January 2021

MakeFlame and Corydalics make their Trancespired Dark debut and have cooked up an amazing tribute.

"2 Th3 Proteus" is dedicated to Proteus, one of Finland's most successful DJs. He is due to end his successful career and the boys decided a tribute was in order. A mixture of genres is key in this mystical journey with psy and tech merging to great effect. Awesome basslines, tough kicks and plenty of entertaining FX lead you to fantastic little hookline which maintains the interest up to the break. The breakdown is lush with a swirling building melody, pads, vocals and little melodic touches captivating your mindspace. The drop kicks things back into the harder area and a secondary hypnotic break elevates the track even further.

Mr Proteus is sure to give his stamp of approval on this fantastic concoction.

------------------------

description:
After a brief period of dormancy, coveted drum and bass label Deception Recordings is back with
another drop of epic proportions, “Control Tower”/“Exhibit A”, courtesy of head honcho Manifest.

Following on from last year’s well-received team-ups “Daybreak” and “Surge” with Dutty Audio boss
BTK and Renegade Hardware affiliate Cold Fusion, the new single finds the South London beatmaker at
the reins once again, flexing his musical muscle over the course of two pulverising steppers.

Named after a local Jamaican business in the celebrated DJ/producer’s hometown of Brixton, opening
gambit “Control Tower” is a boisterous, jungle-infused affair, its introductory dub sirens seeping
through the mix atop a bed of punchy drumwork. Snapping into hard-hitting crescendos centred
around throaty basslines, frantic breakbeats and ricocheting spoken-word samples, it’s a
characteristically hefty affair, primed for deployment in a soundclash.

“Exhibit A”, on the other hand, gets darker, greeting listeners with industrial drones and disquieting
pitched-down vocals before entering a minimal, rhythmic stupor. A prime example of the newfound
capabilities afforded to the seasoned producer as a result of his upgraded studio setup, it’s a technical
triumph, with an array of razor-sharp basslines slicing through at every turn. Serious business.

“Control Tower” / “Exhibit A” hits Beatport and Spotify on 19 July, reaching a full range of stores the
following fortnight on 2 August 2021.

Early Support:  Doc Scott, North Base, Galaxy, BTK, Nicky Black Market,  Drumsound, Logan D, Transforma, Aphrodite, FreqAx, Evol Intent, & More.
➡️19.07.21. ⏯
title: Control Tower - Manifest - Clip

description:
Deception Recordings is back for another climatic. For this release, BTK, Cold Fusion and Manifest come together to bring you two brand new selections on the label. With a friendship which spans over ten years,
being an integral part of the Renegade Hardware Crew, BTK, Cold Fusion and Manifest join forces for a three-way collaboration EP on Deception Recordings. ‘Daybreak’ and ‘Surge’ are guaranteed to cause dancefloor
annihilation and on first listen it’s easy to hear the history between each of the three artists. 

Beginning the first of two tracks is ‘Daybreak’. With heavy drum work, the type of which give the track a serious weight as it crashes into fruition, you become instantly aware of the power which all three artists conjure when they put together their undeniable production standards. Bit by bit you’re taken along for the titanic ride, one engineered with gyrating hooks and a bassline which cuts through the mix undeterred. There’s also intricacy within its madness and before long you’re fully taken along for the ride.

Next up you’re welcomed into the world of ‘Surge’. Following its forerunner, the thumping kick drums punch
through the composition, building layer by layer until it becomes impossible to escape from the freight-train like qualities of this track; it’s one which ensures it never steers away from being the top quality you’d expect from these producers.

This Release is dedicated to Yoko  Speechley & Edward Holmes aka Optiv

Support From: Andy C, Black Sun Empire, Dillinja, Doc Scott, Empress, Evil Intent, Gydra, Maztek, Mob Tactics, Roni Size, Silver, Skynet, State of Mind and many more.

Out Now On Beatport

description:
This week we have the young Zoe Zett from the Frankfurt area.

In the summer of 2021, the paths of our host and you crossed a few times and each time he was totally convinced of your energy and style of play.

As she herself says, she needs a beat to drive her everyday life, and preferably fast. Introduced to music by her parents as a child, she is where she is today at just 19 years old. One of the most popular NewComers in the Rhein Main.

Here we have their part of the series for you ...


𝖗𝖔𝖚𝖌𝖍 𝖈𝖚𝖗𝖊 Podcast Series 042 /w Zoe Zett

Diese Woche haben wir die junge Zoe Zett aus dem Raum Frankfurt.

Im Sommer 2021 haben sich so einige male die Wege unseres Hosts und ihr gekreuzt und jedes mal war er total überzeugt von ihrer Energie und Spielweise.

Wie sie selbst sagt braucht auch in ihrem Alltag einen Beat zum antreiben und dies am besten schnell. Schon im Kindesalter an die Musik durch die Eltern rangeführt, steht sie heute mit ihren gerade mal 19 Jahren da wo sie ist. Einer der beliebtesten NewComer im Rhein Main.

Hier haben wir ihren Teil der Series für euch...

"Awakenings has always been an event that I have admired and have enjoyed on many occasions, so it’s an absolute honour to be able to take part in the podcast series and be given the opportunity to be able to craft 60 minutes of my current favourite tracks. I put my mind into the multiple locations of Awakenings events and used their unique features and infamous traits as inspiration in the curation of my setlist, with the Gashouder dominating my thoughts - using a twist of vocals and slightly dark mesmerising techno. I've also included 3 of my own productions, all of which are set to be released in the coming months. On top of this, there is also a nice mixture of both established and newcomers who make up the remainder of the bill"

We bring you the sounds of Longeez and Sey for our 5th release!

We've got 2 cuts from Bristol's finest - Longeez - since hearing him on the EOW (Earful Of Wax) lockdown stream we've been planning this release so we're very happy to finally be able to release it! A1: Earth - is a melodic start to the EP with a serious B-line underpinning it, whilst A2: Nothin At All comes correct with the mother of all 2nd drops!

On the flip we continue the audio pounding with one half of Bumpy Action (alongside D-Elite), Barry Island's very own Sey. We came across Sey's music on his IG and instantly knew we wanted to own some of his tracks on wax - B1: Imposter and B2: Unruly continue the peak time vibes with chopped vocal samples and clean-cut, shuffling drums, pulling the EP together to create a club ready package!
title: GAT005 Clips

description:
https://gather.bandcamp.com/album/lost-dubs-ep

Man like Jubley returns to the Gather fold with his own EP; Lost Dubs, so called due to the tragedy of his hard drive wiping everything shortly after sending us the pre masters.
These are some of Jubley's sole surviving tracks from that era and we're too gassed to be able to share them with you in the form of a cracking /300 run EP

Premieres will be airing from now until the release date so watch this space!
title: GAT004 A1: Jubley - Rave Crossed Loves

description:
Link to cop: https://gather.bandcamp.com/album/binary-cuts

Fresh off the heels of our 2nd release - Blue Cookie EP - Gather Records are back with Binary Cuts; four heavyweight steppers guaranteed to dismember any dancefloor courtesy of the dynamic duo: On1 and ZeroFG.

A1 “Push” wastes no time getting into some heavyweight, early 00’s style, rib-shattering bass-weight, whilst “Knee Deep” builds the tension to the absolute maximum before letting loose in the fashion that these guys are all too good at.
Over on the flip, the jittering technoid/proto-dubstep style rhythms of “Vexed” seems as though they’re almost designed to bring out the wiggiest moves from dancers with the B2 cut “Final Round” perfectly closing off the EP with skippy beats and spacey atmospherics perfectly primed for those late hour zoners.

These two talented guys have been right at the forefront of the garage resurgence delivering deep, dark rollers that never fail to make you give the gun finger salute and we're very honoured to have them on the label!
tag_list: "uk bass" Dark Electronic Bassline "uk garage" UKG
title: A1:  On1 + ZeroFG -  Push

Max Hawkins is a Ukrainian native of Odessa. Born on July 8, 1993.
When Max was 15 he began to play the piano. Because of his love of music, he always knew that he would connect his life with her. Max takes inspiration from Depeche Mode, as well as other artists such as Stevie Wonder, Pink Floyd, and Ricardo Villalobos. He also drew inspiration from rhythmic South American and Arabic music.
He started to play my music at school parties, for my own pleasure. In 2010, he tried to establish his label, but the project was postponed. Professionally engaged in DJ-ing from 2013 year. The ep was first recorded in 2017 on Comstylez Rec, and in 2019 SAGA's debut album on Quanticman Rec is released.

Max present debut vinyl.

description:
# Jeden Tag ein Set Podcast 089
# by Anahit Vardanyan

Die inzwischen 89. Ausgabe der Jeden Tag ein Set Podcastreihe kommt heute vom sympathischen Multi-Talent Anahit Vardanyan. Nach einem Studium am Klavier in ihrer Heimat Armenien wanderte sie 2016 nach Deutschland aus, um sich dem Studium der Komposition und ersten eigenen Musikproduktionen zu widmen. Sie lernt verschiedene Unterstützer und Akteure der Hamburger Technoszene kennen und beginnt als DJ in Clubs und Bars aufzulegen. Anahit übergibt nach ihren Support-Gigs in kleinen und mittleren Clubs, wie z.B. dem Waagenbau oder Fundbereau, stets volle Floors an ihre DJ Kollegen und macht sich mit ihrem oft harten, aber warmen und teils dramatischen Sound einen Namen als überaus vielversprechende Newcomerin. Sie bespielte bereits zahlreiche Festivals wie das Helene Beach, Oldenbora, Antaris Project sowie auch das Deichbrand Festival u.a. mit Charlottte de Witte, Oliver Huntemann und La Fleur. Ihre ersten, großartigen Releases erschienen auf Labels wie Kitchen Recordings, Hydrozoa, Jannowitz und Made In Brussels. 

Für Jeden Tag ein Set gibt’s nun einen frischen Techno Podcast von Anahit Vardanyan, der von Beginn an mit seinem Groove begeistert und mitreist. Viel Spaß damit!

Anahit Vardanyan findest du unter @anahitvardanyanofficial
Noch mehr Sets findest du auf www.JedenTagEinSet.de
tag_list: "Jeden Tag ein Set" "Anahit Vardanyan" 2021 Podcast 089 Armenien Hamburg
title: Anahit Vardanyan - Jeden Tag Ein Set Podcast 089

description:
# Jeden Tag ein Set Podcast 088
# by BOHO

Innerhalb weniger Jahre legte der Kölner BOHO einen beachtlichen Werdegang hin. Vor allem sein enormer, stets hochqualitativer Output hinterließ Spuren in der Technowelt. Senso Sound, Stil vor Talent, Yoshitoshi oder Octopus Recordings sind nur einige der Labels auf denen er jüngst veröffentlichte. Als Kopf seiner eigenen Imprints Jannowitz und JAW Dropping beweist er zudem regelmäßig selbst einen ausgezeichneten, musikalischen Geschmack und bietet dabei nicht nur bekannten Namen, sondern auch zahlreichen talentierten, aufstrebenden Künstlern eine Plattform. Im November letzten Jahres ging mit EDITION JAW sein inzwischen drittes Label an den Start. Anfang diesen Jahres startet er unter dem Namen 8BOY9 zudem ein neues Projekt mit The Reason Y und Tocadisco, bei dem wir uns auf etwas anderen Sound als sonst freuen dürfen, wie er uns verriet. Wir sind schon sehr gespannt!

Für Jeden Tag ein Set gibt es jetzt einen exklusiven dreistündigen Podcast mit jeder menge Boho-Banger, in dem unter anderem einige anstehenden, sowie unveröffentlichte Tracks enthalten sind. Viel Spaß mit Boho!

BOHO findest du unter @bohojaw
Noch mehr Sets findest du auf www.JedenTagEinSet.de
tag_list: "Jeden Tag ein Set" BOHO Podcast 088 2021 Jannowitz Köln Banger
title: BOHO - Jeden Tag ein Set Podcast 088

description:
# Jeden Tag ein Set Podcast 085
# by Marc DePulse

Marc DePulse ist DJ und Produzent aus Leidenschaft. Bereits über 400 Veröffentlichungen kann er bereits auf seinem Konto verbuchen. Nach seinem Album „Kontrollverlust“ 2017 auf Einmusika, folgten viele weiteren Nummern auf Labels wie Sincopat, Diynamic, Selador, BluFin und vielen mehr. Aktuell steht eine frische EP auf Katermukke in den Startlöchern und zahlreiche Kollaborationen die in nächster Zeit erscheinen werden.

Dabei produziert und spielt Marc DePulse alles was ihm gefällt frei von jeglichem Schubladendenken. Das beweist er auch in seinem neuen Podcast für Jeden Tag ein Set der fernab jeglicher Konvention ist und perfekt für die sonnigen Tage. Viel Spaß mit Marc DePulse!

Marc DePulse findest du unter @marc-depulse
Noch mehr Sets findest du auf www.JedenTagEinSet.de

description:
Ana Antonova is shaping the Croatian scene for more than 15 years in a way that her status is almost indestructible. Her spunky but humble spirit has gained a regional appreciation, and her sense of innovation, the braveness of trying something different has made her more than essential to Croatian up and coming underground territory. Her music can be found on many respectful labels such as Get Physical, Dubøka Records, Not Allowed, THANQ & Dobar House to mention a few. 

She curated an exclusive one-hour mix that explores the different genres within electronic music showcasing her desire to offer a unique musical experience. Sit back, relax and enjoy.
title: SolvdCast 043 by Ana Antonova

description:
On SolvdMag.com https://solvdmag.com/solvdcast-042-aron-volta

Aron Volta came crashing into awareness from relative anonymity in 2019 when he became one of the bestselling deep house artists seemingly overnight. Leading up to this moment were stellar releases on Blind Vision, Madtech, and Pusher Records.

PIV frontman Prunk and label manager Chris Stussy gave the Northern Dutch producer a platform after being blown away by his demo. In the year that followed, Aron Volta became an oracle to many of the PIV artists and even worked as an engineer on some of the music. The Dutchman prepared an exclusive one hour mix of tasty house groovers.
title: SolvdCast 042 by Aron Volta

description:
On SolvdMag.com _ https://solvdmag.com/premiere-mbius

French label Daydream, which is focused on forceful groovy house music exclusively on wax, is ready to launch its 9th release. The previous releases introduced names such as MJOG, Porter, Walker, The Black Tone, Luca Barletta, Barrow, Le Louche, Max Casebolt, Liou, Kepler, The Willers Brothers, and many others.

For its 9th release, Daydream is happy and honored to welcome Mbius, Nick Beringer, Sota and Jerome.c on board. This clubby selection gathers four groovy tunes perfectly balanced between deep dreamy sounds and raw powerful beats.
title: Premiere: Mbius - Qi

description:
On SolvdMag.com https://solvdmag.com/premiere-mbius---jose-nick-beringer-dub

Ethernal is Daydream’s sublabel focused on the micro side of house music with a more intimate approach.
This second chapter is following the same pattern as the first one with Mbius on command. The talented German producer has crafted 3 beautiful tracks full of raw, crispy, and hypnotic modular sounds. As a conclusion, the brilliant Nick Beringer delivers a solid rolling dub remix. The EP will be available in a very limited hand-stamped edition.
tag_list: House "Deep House" Microhouse Premiere SOLVD Magazine
title: Premiere: Mbius - Jose (Nick Beringer Dub)

description:
For our next digital offering we have talented up and comer Sam Alfred, who drops 5 tracks of absolute fire for his debut EP, Strictly Business. Ranging from peak time weapons, dubbed out percussive breaks, heavily swung grooves, dusty Rhodes and a vocal mix thrown in for good measure, this is club-ready music for any dance-floor.

Taking influence from the likes of Chris Stussy, DJ Steaw and Cinthie, Sam has worn his heart on his sleeve all the while managing to carve out his own unique style and has shown us a musical prowess of someone far beyond his years. ​Sam's Strictly Business EP will undoubtably mark him at the top of Melbourne’s one-to-watch list.

All killer, no filler.
credits
releases August 4, 2021

All songs written and produced by Sam Alfred.

Mastered by Corey Kikos.

Additional production and love by Ingrid Parry-Hayden & Ryan Wilson.
title: [LAD006] Sam Alfred - Strictly Business (Previews)

description: Released on Saffron Records, Diary of a Loner is the debut EP by Bristol-based singer-songwriter, Badliana. Born during lockdown, this EP is the “audio notebook” of her experience; an escapism that has resulted in five exciting new tracks. Though it is self reflective in parts, Diary of a Loner is often an exercise in storytelling. With help from her co-writer and producers, MUSSI and Monkey, this EP transverses multiple writing styles and genres throughout, making it an eclectic, and refreshingly fun, debut.
title: Vampire

description:
After his amazing ep on Omerta Records, Bristol based Artificial Red delivers 3 tracks for 3AM Eternal 04. Side A "Mystics" brings the vibes right away! Ambient soundscapes mixed with Hardcore amens and deep subs. Energetic yet meditative B1 "Imy From The Fruit Farm" goes even deeper. Lush ambient pulling you in over subtle breaks, flowing atmospheric jungle. B2 "Dragnet" is another full on amen choppage tune but with subtle guitar licks and wavey atmospherics.

Available for pre-order November 5th -> http://fffmusic.bandcamp.com / Releasedate November 19th
title: Artificial Red - B1 Imy From The Fruit Farm

description:
Bristol based Dancehall don Blackout JA & legendary Jamaican singer Anthony Johnson join forces with New York’s Liondub and Essex based Mr. Quest to present a modern Jungle remake of Johnson’s classic 80’s Reggae hit “Gunshot”. Replete with hard-hitting, energetic drums, deep wobble subs and gritty fresh verses from Blackout, the team are making history internationally. Bristol’s Selecta J-Man ups the ante to complete the package by providing a weighty, absolutely firing stripped back remix of the Ragga anthem. Future classics!

description:
New York's Liondub links once again with the UK's P Skinna to present 'Boiling Hot' from US based Puerto Rican Reggae Dancehall sensation Capital D aka 'Caliente'. Capital D has an impressive history working with a who's who of reggae royalty including combinations with Busy Signal, Luciano, Tarrus Riley and Mykal Rose as well as releases produced by Dean Fraser, DJ Karim (Stainless), Firehouse Crew and Soljie to name a few. Cap has also performed across the world including stage shows at legendary Jamaican events like Reggae Sunsplash, Reggae Sumfest, and 4 appearances at STING internationally.
Up to the time, 'Boiling Hot' is a fresh 4 track EP showcasing Capital D's versatility over modern Dancehall riddims produced by P Skinna & Liondub. Caliente's brilliant, diverse lyrical flavors will appeal to a universal audience and his razor sharp vocal delivery on the EP is guaranteed to leave a lasting impact on the Dancehall world.
title: Capital D - No Time [Prod. P Skinna & Liondub] (Original Mix)

description:
Buy or stream Rebuilding Better Worlds here: http://www.LondonElek.lnk.to/RebuildingBetterWorldsso

Updating the creative spirit of his widely acclaimed 2019 album ‘Building Better Worlds’, London Elektricity revisits his most recent project to date with a specially crafted and hand-picked remix album - ‘Rebuilding Better Worlds’. Featuring an exciting array of artists covering the full drum & bass spectrum, London Elektricity’s latest body of work features remixes from the likes of Cliques, Think Tonk, Logistics, Hugh Hardie, Whiney, Winslow, Seba, Degs & MURIUKI, Mozey & more…

Kickstarting the album with a delicate, soul-drenched liquid drum & bass soother is Hugh Hardie with his remix of original album influencer ‘Build A Better World (feat. Emer Dineen)’. Delving deeper into London Elek’s unique style and Emer’s synesthesic vocals, Hugh crafts heart-wrenching piano melodies and gorgeous rolling breakbeats injecting his signature flavours into the track.

With no clear indication of their true identity, the latest mystery to sweep across the world of drum & bass CLIQUES step up for an addictively feel-good remix of ‘The Prescription Is Love’. With a handful of releases on their own ‘Cliques Collective Audio’, the faceless artist(s) have already taken the scene by storm and their latest remix proves exactly why. Featuring a full live band, expect elevating brass outbursts, Philadelphia strings and blissful vocals.

Quickly gaining a reputation as one of the funniest characters within drum & bass, don’t be fooled by Mozey’s wit and charm. With a fast-growing catalogue of releases spanning labels including Souped Up, Liquid V, Bingo Bass, Serial Killaz and Hospital Records, Mozey’s bass-heavy remix of ‘Funkopolis’ draws upon the playful nature of the original whilst rolling it out into a fizzling drum & bass bouncer.

Legendary in-patient Logistics is on remix duties for ‘Never Trust A Hippy’. Incorporating the melodies and soundscapes from the original, Logistics soon flips the track on its head, turning it into a new-wave liquid funk anthem.

With further contributions from the likes of Think Tonk, Justin Hawkes, Lilac, Digital Native, Villem, Polaris, and a VIP from London Elektricity himself, the carefully curated tracklist brings together a cross-generational and multi-styled selection of artists from across the drum & bass community.

With the original album receiving support from the likes of Mixmag, Magnetic Mag and UKF, as well as being recorded in the immersive Dolby Atmos audio format, London Elektricity shows no signs of slowing down with his latest project. The longevity of his career can be owed to him being the mastermind behind classic Hospital albums including ‘Pull The Plug’, ‘Syncopated City’, ‘Are We There Yet?’ and ‘Yikes!’ (more recently revisited, remastered and repackaged this year as ‘Crikey!’) and London Elektricity continues to push the boundaries of drum & bass with over a quarter-century in the game.

description:
Buy or stream 'Neon Dust' here: http://www.Etherwood.lnk.to/NeonDustso

Melodic master and drum & bass extraordinaire Etherwood makes his album debut on Hospital Records with his fourth long player, ‘Neon Dust’, following on from the successes of his Med School works ‘In Stillness’, ‘Blue Leaves’, and ‘Etherwood’. Across twenty tracks, expect signature liquid drum & bass and Etherwood’s own vocal performances with a fusion of folk, rock, indie-pop, techno, downtempo and ambient delights. Alongside his vast range of musical inspiration, Etherwood’s creativity is evoked through his free spirited mindset, exploring the world in his converted van, dedicated to mindfulness and meditation.

Etherwood and Zara Kershaw present their latest liquid ballad ‘Lighthouse’, a collaboration that will light up the hearts of drum & bass lovers around the world following their powerhouse classic ‘Souvenirs’. This 2021 edition oozes with euphoria and soul with Zara’s enchanting vocals and a smooth amen break coming together to create a jubilant drum & bass masterpiece.

With a nod back to some of his most popular productions like ‘Cast Away’ and ‘Fire Lit Sky’, the irresistibly nostalgic ‘Dahlia’ sees Etherwood’s signature melodies and chord progressions perfectly intertwined. ‘Caliban’ warms the soul with ambient soundscapes, illustrious synth swells, hypnotising vocal chops and crisp rolling drums. Plus, the melodic techno gem ‘Belorama’ that’s destined for the depths of club basements and 5am festival fields.

Embracing his love for alt-pop and indie-electronic styles, ‘Follow The River’ rides through the 140BPM territories welcoming the multitalented Lily Budiasa. Based out of the Gold Coast in Queensland, Australia, Lily also features on ‘Neon Dust’ and ‘Underwater’ and fronts the ambient-folk band TH’FIKA. ‘Follow The River’ is emotive, raw and inspirational with sensual guitar alongside folk-style vocals.

‘We Shine Among The Lights’ is a skippy rock ballad, shining a light on Etherwood’s versatile prowess as a singer, songwriter and multi-instrumentalist. Distorted electric guitars and flanger-drenched drums lay the foundations for Etherwood’s dreamlike vocal harmonies. Not shy of switching up his sound, ‘Water In Your Veins’ and ‘Okusha’ lie at the other end of the spectrum - beautifully stripped back downtempo ambience that elevates the senses.

Other notable moments include the collaboration with the legendary DRS on ‘The Current’, joining forces with Fred V on ‘Nebula’ and working alongside Toronto-based Sigrún Stella on ‘Swans.

With frequent radio support from top-end tastemakers including Annie Mac, MistaJam and Charlie Tee, as well as countless club spins from the likes of Netsky, Sub Focus, Makoto, Degs and Lens, Etherwood’s hugely popular sound takes another step forward in 2021 with his most recent body of work. From topping the iTunes Electronic chart with his second album ‘Blue Leaves’ to performing his very own live session at the prestigious Maida Vale studios, you’ll also be able to find Etherwood at Hospitality Weekend In The Woods, Sundown Festival 2021, ADE Hospitality and Hospitality Bristol this year.

With a nod back to some of his most popular productions like ‘Cast Away’ and ‘Fire Lit Sky’, the irresistibly nostalgic ‘Dahlia’ sees Etherwood’s signature melodies and chord progressions perfectly intertwined. ‘Caliban’ warms the soul with ambient soundscapes, illustrious synth swells, hypnotising vocal chops and crisp rolling drums. Plus, the melodic techno gem ‘Belorama’ that’s destined for the depths of club basements and 5am festival fields.

Embracing his love for alt-pop and indie-electronic styles, ‘Follow The River’ rides through the 140BPM territories welcoming the multitalented Lily Budiasa. Based out of the Gold Coast in Queensland, Australia, Lily also features on ‘Neon Dust’ and ‘Underwater’ and fronts the ambient-folk band TH’FIKA. ‘Follow The River’ is emotive, raw and inspirational with sensual guitar alongside folk-style vocals.

‘We Shine Among The Lights’ is a skippy rock ballad, shining a light on Etherwood’s versatile prowess as a singer, songwriter and multi-instrumentalist. Distorted electric guitars and flanger-drenched drums lay the foundations for Etherwood’s dreamlike vocal harmonies. Not shy of switching up his sound, ‘Water In Your Veins’ and ‘Okusha’ lie at the other end of the spectrum - beautifully stripped back downtempo ambience that elevates the senses.

Other notable moments include the collaboration with the legendary DRS on ‘The Current’, joining forces with Fred V on ‘Nebula’ and working alongside Toronto-based Sigrún Stella on ‘Swans.

With frequent radio support from top-end tastemakers including Annie Mac, MistaJam and Charlie Tee, as well as countless club spins from the likes of Netsky, Sub Focus, Makoto, Degs and Lens, Etherwood’s hugely popular sound takes another step forward in 2021 with his most recent body of work. From topping the iTunes Electronic chart with his second album ‘Blue Leaves’ to performing his very own live session at the prestigious Maida Vale studios, you’ll also be able to find Etherwood at Hospitality Weekend In The Woods, Sundown Festival 2021, ADE Hospitality and Hospitality Bristol this year.
