description:
LF RMX 024

A - Humano - Death (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)
B - Inigo Kennedy - NGC6826 Blinking Eye (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)

For this latest entry into the LFRMX-catalogue Len Faki has chosen two synth-driven tracks of anthemic proportions. Reeko, also known as Architectural, with only one release under his Humano-guise, gets picked for its dramatic strings and larger-than-life stabs, slowly building towards a driving momentum, taking on the peak time with style.
The flip sports mainstay Inigo Kennedy, whose original track built heavily on atmospheric IDM-breakbeats, but works just as well with a straight corset issued by Faki, now highlighting the poetic synth work at its core even more.

Bandcamp: bit.ly/LFRMX_024
www.straßenkinder-ev.de
www.lfrmx.com
tag_list: humano, reeko architectural "inigo kennedy" "len faki" remixes edits Techno electronic berlin
title: Humano - Death (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)

description:
LF RMX 023

A - Robert Armani - Hit Hard (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)
B - Musik Aus Strom - A2 Untitled (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)	

More unheard edits from Len Faki‘s personal vaults on this release, harking way back to the mid-'90s and their relentless, hard-hitting styles.
 
Chicago legend Robert Armani, also still hailed as one of the originators of hardstyle by many, makes an appearance on the A-side. And it‘s that characteristic, punishing kick sound, which is still present in the modern edit, carrying on the original‘s obtuse force albeit shrouded in a much more ominous and austere veil.
 
German IDM-duo Funkstörung well left their mark on the millennium’s last decade. Even with their side-project Musik Aus Strom that restricted itself to a series of forward-pointing, no-nonsense acid-techno albums. Len Faki picks out a track showcasing the raw and vital essence of that Acid Planet-time and molds it into a soaring, sizzling and well-balanced tool, tricky and perky at once. 

www.lfrmx.com

description:
A1 - Mod21 - Epilogue 4 (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)
A2 - Mod21 - Epilogue 1 (Len Faki Deepspace Mix)
B - Irakli - 34 Choices Of Gender (Len Faki Hardspace Mix)
	
On his newest triplet, Len Faki lets loose alien-induced sounds and strange frequencies from far outer space. The A-side goes for Mod21, an enigmatic Italien whose instinct for building a sketchy vibe shines through too on Faki‘s remixes. They‘re both radiant,
sparkling from somewhere buried deep down, their hollowed-out drums and crisp sonics conjuring up an orbital charge! The flip boasts a beefed-up version of Irakli‘s 34 Choices of Gender, its bassline subtly morphing underneath a string of complex net of woven sounds. A slowly brewing vortex finally discharged in true Faki fashion.

Bandcamp: http://bit.ly/LFRMX022
www.lfrmx.com
www.straßenkinder-ev.de

description:
LF RMX 021

A1 - Skymn - Biker Scene (Len Faki Deepspace Mix)
A2 - Refracted - Depth Charge (Len Faki Deepspace Mix)
B1 - Craft - Time Will Tell (Len Faki Deepspace Mix)
B2 - A Sacred Geometry  - At The Gates (Len Faki Deepspace Mix)

For the first time, Len Faki decides to dish out a full foursome of his Deepspace-mixes, sharing one of the most profound entries into the series yet. Originally released within the last couple of years. The atmospheric and dubbed-out ’Biker Scene’ is one of riding blissfully under a sky illuminated by the milky way, followed by a streamlined update on the soaring metallic shuffle that is ’Depth Charge’, its tribal undertones prowling in the underbrush. The flip tucks NYC‘s Craft‘s wild synth work into a tight corset, channeling its lively energy even more effectively for the floor. Closing out with A Sacred Geometry, the Berlin/Rome-connection‘s finely plucked synths glide above elated pads and a skittering rhythm.

The proceeds of this record will be forwarded entirely to charity organization Straßenkinder e.V., who are working to offer help to the children living on the streets of Berlin.

Bandcamp: http://bit.ly/LFRMX_021
www.lfrmx.com

description:
here is a download gift / sneak tease for the fans, to show the kind of quality I'm extracting from my old cassettes using mega high quality cassette decks.
Because I've added vari-speed, I get to choose what speed I encode them at, I've done a few different versions of all my fave ones and it's usually just what I think sounds good at the time or just different to what I'm used to.
This one is from a That's cassette labelled copy III , i used a lot of the VX90 tapes in that period of my life.
It is the 12th track on side a.
Even though I used to write COPY *.number, they were actually the original masters.
Think was one of the first tracks that had a small section with intentional microtuning, [harmonic series sec]
Encoded with Nakamichi CR7e cassette deck.

+added, it cuts out at the end coz the tape ran out :)
I remember sometimes recording tracks to cassettes, I'd be looking at the cassette nearing the end and try and finish the track before the tape ran out :)
bit different from todays recording methods .

description: Mexican based label BLDSMX returns with their second compilation 'Armada Sounds 002,' boasting a variety of hybrid bass music from international producers. Today we premiere the high energy rave banger "Hands Up" by Hong Kong producer Kray. With previous releases on akin labels like China's Unchained Asia and U.S based SHOOT recordings, the young producer is expanding their sound with each release. The full compilation drops October 2nd, and includes a stacked line up of FWJ faves like Groves, Sideswipe, Greazus, Golden, HNGVR, Danky, Mars Kasei, Raptorhandz, Digid, and many more...
title: [PREMIERE] Kray-Hands Up (BLDSMX)

description: Sublimate's first compilation album is an eclectic collection of 18 tunes from 24 different artists across 7 countries. The Portland based label and event showcases an inclusive range of styles touching on Drum & Bass, Dubstep, Jungle, Halftime, West Coast Bass, and Leftfield bass.  NO matter your speed or style, there's a tune in here for you! Today we are excited to premiere the acid infused 160 Banger " We Craft Jamz" a collab from Samsara Beats Bossman HNGVR and Sardinia's UnoTurbo thats guaranteed to get the dancefloor hopping. This tune and the whole comp will be available on the "RECLAMATION" compilation, out everywhere October 18th!
title: [PREMIERE]HNGVR X UnoTurbo - We Craft Jamz(Sublimate)

description:
Germany's Defrostatica Records is slated to release "Hybrid Hooks" a monster 21 track compilation of uptempo club and rave bangers. The compilation  boasts an international line up of long standing
and new artists of Defrostatica Records such as Sinistarr, HomeSick, MorganNeiman, Greazus, Klose, Sam Binga, Jon1st, Sun People, Kiat, Anna Morgan, Detroit’s Filthiest, BSN Posse, Kabuki, Yazzus, Dispondant, Agzilla, Maltin Worf, DJ YumYum, Arcane, DJ Badshape, d’cure, Alza 54 and Jermainesoul.
The Leipzig label continues to blur the boundaries between jungle, footwork, juke and drum and bass with this collection of tunes. Each artist included was chosen for their work representing a refined sound identity within their cultural and musical context. This dynamic of diversity, inclusivity and mutual influence marks the DNA of Defrostatica.
Today we are excited to premiere "Orange Sunset" a lush collab between Iberian Juke founders BSN Posse and renowned multi-genre beat-smith Kabuki. Follow the "Buy" link to pre-order and get a glimpse of the rest of this hefty compilation, full release July 16 out everywhere!
title: [PREMIERE]BSN Posse & Kabuki -Orange Sunset (Defrostatica Records)

description:
Hybrid bass music is an international movement connecting passionate producers and listeners from all over the globe. The sound may be niche but the community is mighty. Mexico City label and party BLDSMX, kicks off their EP series with "Make Your Body Hot," four eclectic tracks of rave bangers by Italian producer Frame. 
Today we premiere "Make your body hot," the title track which also features fellow member of Italy's The Dreamers collective, Treega. Together they create a peak dance floor weapon, pulling from hardcore, juke, and DnB. The release also includes a dark remix of the track by BLDSMX member Aiokai. Out everywhere June 25th, follow the buy link to their Bandcamp to purchase!
title: [PREMIERE] Frame & Treega- Make Your Body Hot(BLDSMX)

description:
Two big influences of mine for the longest time have been 90s gangster rap and mainstream hardcore. Since first discovering mainstream hardcore as a very young teen, I've always wanted to try my hand at making something of this style-- something dark, gritty, and gangster as fuck. Now that my production abilities are at a certain level, I finally feel confident that I can scratch that itch & do this style justice. Not to mention the melody for this track had been stuck in my mind for several months. When an idea for a track sticks around for that long, that's how you know you have to make it a reality.

Download this track: 
https://distrokid.com/hyperfollow/neoqor/clear-em-out

description:
As I have been unable to have a mix for several months due to lockdown I thought I would upload this mix that I did several years ago with my good mate Nathan.  First 20-30 minutes or so is a whistle stop tour through 94-96, with the majority of the tunes being from 97-99.  The odd sloppy mix here and there but considering it is a 2 hour mix with 30 tunes, no planning, and a fair amount of alcohol, it came out alright I reckon!

Hope you enjoy:

description:
Coming in hella strong, Bristol-based producer/DJ @longeez takes the bass-baton and supplies us with two outrageous club heaters for ec2a-35. With this release, he is sure to retain such a rep as he dives straight in with wob-heavy ‘Hol’ Tight’ held together by jumpy melodic synth sounds, shifting vocal samples and some deep-seated whirs. ‘Keep Movin’ does what it says on the tin and is reminiscent of UKG pioneer ‘El-B’ with a 2-steppy twist alongside an eerie backdrop - old school vibe with new school tactics. 

Available exclusively via : www.ec2aworldwide.com
title: Longeez - Hol' Tight
